This Resource defines opaque data that can be transfered between
endpoints where the data itself is not interpretable by the OCF
endpoints. The stringdata is a string of ASCII characters.
This Property contains the opaque data.
This Property describes the encoding of the payload, e.g. binary as
This Property describes the identification of the payload, e.g. what
The size in bytes of the decoded binary object.
The hash code of the blob. If present, it is used to check the
decoded content of the object data point for integrity. The algorithm
used for generating the hash value is SHA-2 [15]. The data point
contains the hash as a hex encoded value.
The eco system that is using the payload.
